content.detailedDescription:
I was in my back yard smoking one last cigarette for the night in my back porch door way. looking into the sky towards the ne and scrolling toward the se then back when 4 white lights were seen in my e corner of my back yard hovering about 10-15 feet above the ground and on my side of the trees. the lights were in a straight line and all spaced evenly apart. they did not illuminate anything in the yard. all appeared at the same time and disappeared at the same time lasting about 2-3 seconds. there was no noise, no solid object and no wind shift. i looked up to the sky, then scanned to the se and saw a row of 4 lights evenly spaced in a straight line about an inch long at arms length. they disappeared quickly with out movement as well.

off in the distance to the e is a flashing cell tower that is about the height of the lights in my yard and due to the trees on my fence line it is not always flashing in my eye. i have played with it many times, trying to get it to show me the same 4 lights. the stutters stay in the same vicinity and either bounce around it or in a line down and it all flashes in a quick sequence not at all like what i witnessed. i can't make sense of it no matter what i do and i can't recreate it.
content.summary: 4 white lights appeared in my back yard.

content.detailedDescription: I was home watching tv in my bed when i saw a light, and then noticed i was in a house i had moved out of 8 years ago. i was looking at the time on my phone when the lights went out. i sat on the couch and saw a reflection of a figure who was at least 6 ft tall. there were 2 if them in what looked like military uniforms. they had broad shoulders, thin neck, large head, long arms, and 4 fingers on each hand. they spoke to me, and i understood them. they wanted to take tissue samples. one from my leg, one from my abdomen, and one from my,right breast. i fought and screamed (i have a fear of needles) and was told it was ok. they would just leave with the other 2 samples. i was then released and returned to my current home. they next morning i started bleeding (my menstrual cycle had started earl for no reason) and thought it was very odd. to this day i can still see them in my mind.
content.summary: Possible abduction

content.detailedDescription: I noticed a green ball of light looking to the northwest. i thought it was a meteorite until it changed direction and shot straight up then stopped and then headed west.  no flashing lights. just a green ball of light travelling faster than anything i have ever seen before. it was just at dusk and there were no stars or airplanes in the sky

content.detailedDescription: On 11/28/2014 at approximately 7:35 pm i was walking my dog outside of my home, was looking up at the moon as it was a very clear sky with many stars.   i noticed a ball or orb of bright red to fire orange it was coming from the south it was heading north in the sky it made no noise it seamed to change size as it brightened and dimmed. at first i thought it might be a meteor because of the red orange fire color. but it moved to slowly and then i saw it was changing directions heading to the east. i watched the orb for another minute as it headed east until it faded out of sight. i was going to take a picture but i had not taken my cell phone out with me on my walk, i wish i had. i have seen many jets and other types of aircraft in the daytime and nighttime skies this was like none them that i have ever seen in the sky before. after seeing this object i went in and told my wife of what i had seen in the sky outside of our home. i have seen other ufo objects in my life this makes the fifth one in my life time.
content.summary: Red to fire orange object taveling north, turned slowly to the east no sound was heard

content.detailedDescription: I was on my back porch having a cigarette and looking at the blue sky to my left when i observed a bright, shiny silver disc with an appendage on top...Making it look like a hat.  i believe it was mufon that went to mexico city to interview jaime and one of his witnesses to many ufo events and who took many pictures of these events.  mufon debunked this young man's cell phone picture of the same ufo i saw, i believe it was frenchtown, nj or an adjacent town that it was flying over.  it looked as though it was heading to bucks county, pa.  i live 6 blocks from the bridge leading into bucks county.  if it was mufon that debunked this young man's cell phone picture...They made a big mistake.  unfortunately i do not have a camera or a cell phone, otherwise it would be standing proof that jaime's witness was correct. it seemed to disappear...Not dematerialize...I just lost sight of it.
content.summary: Bright silver disc with round appendage on top, looked like a hat.

content.detailedDescription: Me and my husband were standing outside our balcony and all of the sudden a bright object in the sky just appeared and seemed to be moving rather quickly. it was going back and fourth, straight up into the sky, and then falling back down at unseemly high speeds. it had a red light and a green light rotating between colors and then the light became white! when we first saw it we thought it was just a plane but then it would suddenly stop and drop low and planes don't do that. the neighbors that also saw it said it didn't seem right. we felt confused at what it could be it seems to get closer and further within seconds apart. we finally lost sight of it when it dropped down really low behind trees and didn't see it again after that. while watching this happen we felt as if it was unreal and we definitely knew it wasn't just a plane, they can't move in those directions at a rapid speed!  can someone explain this phenomenon?  and what is the significance?
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Flying object with lights going back and fourth in all directions

content.detailedDescription: This subject was observed by myself and two other individuals on a clear night. 11/27/14 it started as a cool night observing the sky when i thought i was looking at mars' orange light glow, then it moved to my right "as i was facing south" in a blur flashing brilliant white light, coming to a stop shortly after and glowing orange again then shortly after taking off into the distance with its orange light fading.
content.summary: Bright light stationary in the sky orange in color changed direction moving southwest in a strait line and flashed brilliant white light in the process then back to orange before taking off into the distance unseen sky.

content.detailedDescription: We were outside around 8pm on nov 26th 2014 viewing the stars through a pair of generation 5 military night vision goggles mounted to a helmet a friend who is a helicopter pilots uses.   while viewing the stars this triangular object came into view.  the object was not visible to the naked eye as i had 4 other people with me taking turns with the goggles.  i asked if they could see what i see as i thought maybe if it was an aircraft of some sort it's lights would be visible on such a clear night.  no one could see anything but me because of the goggles.  the object had a dull round light towards each point of the triangle but contained within the object not attached to the edge.  these round dull lights were fairly large probable taking up 25% to 30% of each point.   this was definitely a solid object.  it moved about the same speed as an airplane but hard to determine the altitude which makes it hard to determine it's actual size.  it moved in a straight line across the sky directly above me, passed and disappeared into the horizon after a slight move to the right.  this object did not seem to have any sort of jet engine in the back, no additional lights except the 3 i spoke of earlier.  there was also no sign of any propeller either.  no noise, just silence.
content.summary: Observed a trianglur shaped object with 3 dim lights traveling across night sky through night vision goggles.  unable to see with the naked eye.

content.detailedDescription: While cooking dinner 35 stories above ground in east york toronto i gazed out the window. i saw what appeared to be the hugest red crescent moon i've ever seen. i took a picture, messaged my brother and as i watched it started to fade away. the left(south) side fading first until just a red 'tip' on the north side was visible. it was the last part to fade to black. my apartment faces due west and due to the height i can see all the way to mississauga on a clear night like tonight. i could see the clouds, but it definitely wasn't cloud cover blocking the glow. then i realized at this time of night the moon should be in the east or overhead, not west and hovering on the horizon. this thing was massive. i could see it on either side of various apartment buildings on the horizon. it appeared to be more than a km or 2 wide (perhaps more). and was a reddish orange colour. it steadily faded , no flickering or flashing. it truly looked like an eclipsing planet. i was transfixed by it. couldn't walk away in case i missed it. only looked away for quick texts to my brother hoping he could see what i was seeing. left me with goosebumps.
content.summary: I thought it was the moon. but it was on the western horizon too early in the evening. huge low crescent shape that faded before my eyes in under 5 minutes

content.detailedDescription:
During thanksgiving night, after me and my mother enjoyed a brief dinner at t.G.I.Friday's, we decided to leave early to catch a train south along route 309. at 7:10pm, while riding in the passenger seat, i looked towards the eastern night sky and noticed a group of dim, deep orange lights. 

at first i mistook them for radio tower lights, but when our car came to rest at a stop light, i realized they were moving south at a slow speed. looking ahead of us were another group of orange lights more sparsely spaced, and they appeared to be at the same altitude as the eastern group but instead moving to the east. i was first perplexed, near to a point of panic, then became excited after entertaining the possibility the lights were ufo's. 

one of the western group lights had one to two smaller, very dim white lights flying around it. it was the middle-most light i believe.

they were in the sky for a good two-three minutes after first noticing the eastern group. simple awe-struck prevented me from taking my low-quality camera phone out, but when i tried and looked back up, only two of the five lights remained. either the rest vanished or turned off their lights, and maybe fifteen seconds later the rest were gone. looking back north a minute later i saw one of the western group lights again with a small airplane further up in altitude, but closer to us who were further south.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Two groups of five orange lights slowly moving across route 309

content.detailedDescription:
This occurred on november 25th,2014 at around 6:55pm.
  

  i left the house with a flash light, going out to check on the level of the creek because we were having flood warnings and the creek was at the top of its banks from heavy rains. i was standing in the dark, the clouds very low, about 500 ft. it was very quiet with the sounds of the creek water coming to me on the air.  looking south i was moving my flash light from side to side, trying to see the water on the fields more clearly when suddenly a very bright light from the southwesterly sky was upon me.  in that instant i was bathed in a brilliant, white light.  i could see the colors of my jacket and shirt, even my own right hand holding the flash light out in front of me.  i looked up to see where the light was coming from.  in a field about 1,500 feet away from where i was, below the clouds, hovering in the air soundlessly was a round object with the bottom pointing toward me so it appeared elliptical.  the edges were softly rounded, kind of like a thin inner tube, and except for the edge of the object, the entire bottom was lit up.  it was like being in a huge spot light, the beam widening around me, narrower where it came from the object.  in half a second the beam of light was shut off and all i saw was the bottom of the object, still lit up.  the object never moved but remained stationary. then half a second later the entire object blinked out leaving me in darkness, except for my flash light that was still on.  dazed, i looked around myself in the night.  then i looked north where the mill lights were reflecting off the bottom of the clouds.  about three to five seconds later, beyond the mill and somewhere out in what would have been the horizon on a clear night,i heard a muffled 'boom' and an then extremely brilliant blue light lit up the entire sky from one side of the valley to the other.  it appeared as if the mill's lights were briefly turned off during that moment of blue light. then afterward the mill's lights appeared again as normal and as if nothing had happened.  the sound and the brilliant blue light made me think the two were connected.  i wondered if something might have crashed and caused the light.  then i thought about what i'd seen above the field.  were all of these things connected with one another?
content.summary: i was outside walking at night, when a bright light shone upon me.  i looked up to see the source and saw an eliptical object then it blinked out.

content.detailedDescription:
Outside having a smoke at appr. 2130 hours. a typical dark crystal clear night in texas, as later confirmed with goggles.

fuzzy white object was moving north. similar to a comet, with poorly defined edges and a tail. however the object was moving at tremendous speed similar to a shooting star. object made a 90 degree right turn, continued north for a moment, and back to the left at a right angle. then lost sight. the turns were not perfect 90 degrees but close, in fact they were 'rounded off' right angle turns at very high rate of speed.

content.detailedDescription: I was driving home after hanging out with some friends at about 10:30pm.  i had just turned onto 315 n from bethal rd in columbus oh, when i noticed what appeared to be a bar of lights in the sky above the road.  at first i thought it was some kind of airplane.  i kept looking at it and it did not move like an airplane would.  it just kind of hovered in the sky above the road.  it was quite large and i tried to notice if there was more to it then the lights.  i grabbed my phone and thought about trying to take a picture but then remembered that i was driving and decided against a photo attempt.  then i thought about pulling off the road to get a better look.  then i thought, what if i get abducted?  as i passed under the object i continued to look in my mirrors to get a second look but could see nothing in my rear view or side view mirrors.  i got home and felt excited at what i saw and dissappointed that i did not investigate further.  i told my wife about my experience and she kind of laughed at me.  what i saw was strange, unlike any aircraft that i have seen before.  it did not move.  i have traveled that same road at night hundreds of times and i have never seen anything like what i saw tonight.
content.summary: Unidentified object hovering above the freeway

content.summary: A bright solid luminescent, yellow, chevron shaped object the size of the moon
